        <header class="header">
        <h1 id="top">Review Process</h1>
        <p class="intro-text"><em>MIS Quarterly</em> is committed to a rigorous, fair, and developmental peer review process.</p>
        </header>
        <div class="layout">
        <!-- Sticky sidebar: Related Policies -->
        <nav class="toc" aria-label="Related policies">
        <div class="toc-title">Related Policies</div>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://misq.umn.edu/policies#s2">Anonymous Review</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://misq.umn.edu/policies#s4-5">Research Transparency</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://misq.umn.edu/policies#s4-5">Data Rights and Provenance</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://misq.umn.edu/policies#s5">Accepted Papers</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://misq.umn.edu/pages/submission_guidelines">Guidelines for Revision</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://misq.umn.edu/policies#s3">Resubmissions of Rejected Papers</a></li>
        </ul>
        </nav>
        <!-- Main content -->
        <main class="content" id="content" role="main">
        <!-- 1. Commitment -->
        <section id="commitment" class="section">
        <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
        <p>Peer review at <em>MIS Quarterly</em> is rigorous and constructive. Reviews are focused on improving scholarship while maintaining the highest standards of quality and fairness.</p>
        </section>
        <!-- 2. Anonymous Review -->
        <section id="anonymous" class="section">
        <h2>Anonymous Review</h2>
        <p><em>MIS Quarterly</em> uses a double‑anonymous process: authors and reviewers remain unknown to one another to support impartiality and fairness. Editors are aware of author identities to manage the process, but this information is not shared with reviewers.</p>
        </section>
        <!-- 3. Roles -->
        <section id="roles" class="section">
        <h2>Roles in the Process</h2>
        <h3>Authors</h3>
        <p>Submit original research that advances the field and respond constructively and thoroughly to editorial and reviewer feedback.</p>
        <h3>Reviewers</h3>
        <p>Provide timely, rigorous, and developmental evaluations that add value and help authors maximize the potential of their work.</p>
        <h3>Associate Editors (AEs)</h3>
        <p>Coordinate peer review, synthesize reviewer input, and make a recommendation to the SE.</p>
        <h3>Senior Editors (SEs)</h3>
        <p>Make the final editorial decision and ensure consistency, fairness, and quality.</p>
        <h3>Transparency Editor</h3>
        <p>Oversees research transparency requirements and expectations.</p>
        </section>
        <!-- 4. Flow -->
        <section id="flow" class="section">
        <h2>Peer Review Flow</h2>
        <p>Manuscripts undergo an initial review by a Senior Editor and Associate Editor, followed by peer review from external reviewers. The Associate Editor and reviewer feedback helps guide the Senior Editor’s decision.</p>
        <div class="callout">
        <strong>At a glance:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>External reviewers: 0–3</li>
            <li>Initial decision timeline: ~3–5 months</li>
            <li>Fee to submit: $0</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <figure class="figure" aria-label="Peer Review Flow Diagram">
        <img src="/ImageLibrary/Capstone.png" data-full="/ImageLibrary/Capstone.png" alt="MIS Quarterly Peer Review Flowchart" class="zoomable" />
